  o Major features (SOCKS proxy, self-hosted use):
    - Add a new "SocksExitByUser" option that lets a single SocksPort
      route each SOCKS5-authenticated stream to the exit country named by
      its SOCKS5 username, via the new "SocksExitUserMap" option (a CSV of
      "username={routerset}" entries, e.g. "jp={jp},de={de}"). Username
      "jp" with any password pins that stream's exit to a single relay in
      {jp}; if the user's country has no usable exit relay, the stream is
      rejected immediately instead of falling back to another country or
      waiting out SocksTimeout. Passwords are never checked by Tor, so any
      value works. Designed for self-hosted/internal use; do not expose
      this on an untrusted network, as it reintroduces .exit-style exit
      selection surface. Closes ticket 00000.
